Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced that the record for the COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has risen to 24077. 779 new cases were recorded today. The centre made this known via its Twitter handle. The new cases per states are listed below: Lagos-285 Rivers-68 FCT-60 Edo-60 Enugu-56 Delta-47 Ebonyi-42 Oyo-41 Kaduna-19 Ogun-18 Ondo-16 Imo-12 Sokoto-11 Borno-9 Nasarawa-8 Abia-5 Gombe-5 Kebbi-5 Kano-4 Yobe-3 Ekiti-3 Osun-2 779 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-285Rivers-68FCT-60Edo-60Enugu-56Delta-47Ebonyi-42Oyo-41Kaduna-19Ogun-18Ondo-16Imo-12Sokoto-11Borno-9Nasarawa-8Abia-5Gombe-5Kebbi-5Kano-4Yobe-3Ekiti-3Osun-2 24,077 confirmed8,625 discharged558 deaths pic.twitter.com/JsOtNeFSDx — NCDC (@NCDCgov) June 27, 2020   With the total of 24,077 confirmed COVID-19 cases in Nigeria,  8,625 patients have been discharged across the country while 558 lives have been lost to the virus.